entities.name: Atom to Quark Transfer Task
entities.description: User request to transfer Atom to Quark knowledge from mcp-knowledge-graph to mcp-memvid system

observations.text:
**ATOM TO QUARK KNOWLEDGE TRANSFER COMPLETED - June 9, 2025**

**TASK**: Transfer all Atom to Quark knowledge from mcp-knowledge-graph to mcp-memvid knowledge graph system.

**FINDINGS**: 
• Located "Atom to Quark" project in mcp-knowledge-graph (ID: 85f7645f-b3ef-4ff4-98f9-0dbd87441499)
• Project exists but is completely empty - zero entities, relationships, or observations
• No knowledge content available to transfer

**ACTIONS COMPLETED**:
✅ Created new "Atom to Quark" project in mcp-memvid system (ID: aced1846-ab9a-46ae-a489-9efb070eb1dc)
✅ Added comprehensive description covering atomic to quantum particle journey
✅ Project is ready for knowledge population

**STATUS**: Transfer task complete. Original project was empty, so new project created and ready for user to populate with atomic physics and quantum mechanics knowledge.

**NEXT STEPS**: User can now add entities about atoms, electrons, protons, neutrons, quarks, leptons, and fundamental forces to the new project.

entities.name: Server Startup Issues
entities.description: Updated description for testing

observations.text: Common Startup Problems: ClassNotFoundException for missing Quark classes, NoSuchMethodError for changed method signatures, property placeholder resolution failures like NumberFormatException, bean instantiation problems, JNDI resource access failures

Common Solutions: Use @Value annotations for property resolution, replace WorkManagerTaskExecutor with ThreadPoolTaskExecutor, ensure component scanning includes org.tiaa.quark packages, configure PropertySourcesPlaceholderConfigurer bean, check web.xml for correct context configuration

entities.name: Atom Framework
entities.description: TIAA's legacy framework with XML-based configuration, monolithic architecture

observations.text: Framework Characteristics: XML-based configuration using applicationContext.xml and servletContext.xml. Supports Spring 4+ versions. Monolithic architecture with tightly coupled components. Key annotations: @EnableAtomWeb, @EnableAtomProfile, @EnableAtomContent, @EnableAtomWebSecurity

entities.name: Quark Framework
entities.description: TIAA's modern framework with annotation-based Java configuration, modular architecture

observations.text: Framework Requirements: Requires Spring 5.2.0+ and Gradle 7.4.2+. Modular architecture with independent libraries: user-profile-common, user-profile-planfocus, content-management, web-security-management, entitlement-management, preference-management
